      "meaning": "one who submits / Muslim (male)",
      "rootArabic": "س ل م",
      "rootMeaning": "peace, submission, safety",
      "frequencyInQuran": 37,
      "specialNote": "مُسْلِم is masculine. Add ة (ta marbuta) to make it feminine: مُسْلِمَة. This -ah ending is the most common feminine marker in Arabic.",
      "ayahCards": [
        {
          "surahName": "Al-Baqarah",
          "surahNumber": 2,
          "ayahNumber": 132,
          "arabicText": "وَلَا تَمُوتُنَّ إِلَّا وَأَنتُم مُّسْلِمُونَ",
          "translation": "And do not die except while you are Muslims.",
          "highlightedWordArabic": "مُّسْلِمُونَ",
          "audioUri": "audio://quran/default/2/132"
        }
      ]
    },
