      "arabic": "مُسْلِمَة",
      "transliteration": "muslima",
      "meaning": "Muslim woman",
      "rootArabic": "س ل م",
      "rootMeaning": "peace, submission, safety",
      "frequencyInQuran": 8,
      "specialNote": "The ة at the end (ta marbuta) marks this word as feminine. It is pronounced as a 't' before a vowel in connected speech.",
